<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_File_Transfer_Adapter_Abstract does not handle file uploads when no file is uploaded by the user.</p>

<p>Example code</p>

<pre class="literal">
$f = new Zend_Form();
$f-&gt;addElement('file', 'photo', array(
    'label' =&gt; 'photo',
    'required'=&gt; false
))
  -&gt;addElement('submit', 'save', array('label' =&gt; 'btn_save'));

if($_POST &amp;&amp; $f-&gt;isValid($_POST)) {
  echo 'valid';
}

echo $f-&gt;render(new Zend_View());
</pre>

<p>Exception is thrown when form is submitted: "photo" not found by file transfer adapter 
The problem is on line 572, Zend/File/Transfer/Adapter/Abstract.php, where validation does not consider option ignoreNoFile for the adapter.</p>

